Step 1: Calculate Gross Profit Margin.
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%
• From the income statement, Gross Profit = 1,340,513.79 and Total Revenue = 6,920,513.79.
• Therefore, Gross Profit Margin = (1,340,513.79 / 6,920,513.79) × 100% ≈ 19.36%

Step 2: Calculate Cash Flow to Debt Ratio.
• In the provided sample the ratio was computed as Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities divided by Total Current Liabilities.
• From our cash flow statement, Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = –5,714,107.45.
• From our balance sheet, Total Current Liabilities = 2,736,025.72.
• Therefore, Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = –5,714,107.45 / 2,736,025.72 ≈ –2.09

Thus, the final answer is:

{
  "solution": {
    "Gross Profit Margin": "19.36%",
    "Cash Flow to Debt Ratio": "-2.09"
  }
}
